observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
a. concurrent Municipal GSO to coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to prepare the road map of the Municipality to facilitate the preparation of inventory and reporting of the Municipality’s road network system;
b. Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Concurrent Municipal GSO the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and thereafter;
c. Municipal Accountant to record the amount of road networks equivalent to the required transition provision percentage every year starting from CY 2016 to CY 2019.

We recommended management the following:

a] Issue official receipt to the concerned barangays the amount of ₱190,300.00 to support their disbursements;
b] Demand for the immediate recovery of the ₱190,300.00 from the collecting officer; 
c]  Recognize in the books the accountability of the designated collector Mr. Edward Quijalvo and effect adjustments in the books of accounts; and
d] Require Mr. Quijalvo to settle his outstanding balance before issuing his clearance for money and property accountability.  Failure to do so will make the approving/signing authority primary or jointly liable for the amount given as provided under Sections 102 and 104 of  P.D. 1445.

We recommended to management the following:

a] 	Recognize in the books these collectibles from the operation of water system totaling ₱418,319.47 as well as rentals from delinquent stall occupants amounting to ₱255,468.75 for fair presentation of the financial reports;  
b] 	Strictly enforce collection strategies such as waterline disconnection to avoid accumulation of uncollected water bills; 
c] 	Business license should not be renewed unless back rentals be first settled; and
d]  Send demand letters to these delinquent concessionaires/consumers as well as stall occupants compelling them to immediately settle their balances.

We recommended that management:

a] Require the concerned NGOs/POs who were recipients of the fund transfer/financial assistance totalling ₱150,000.00 to submit final fund utilization report duly certified by the concerned officers together with the inspection report and certificate of project completion issued by LGU official; 
b] Adjust the Donations account or the Government Equity account and take up the Due from NGOs/POs in the account corresponding to the fund assistance and furnish the Audit Team a copy of the journal entry voucher pertaining to the adjustments;
c] Require the submission of liquidation report by the implementing NGOs/POs; and
d] Ensure completeness of the documentary requirements enumerated under COA Circular 2007-001 prior and after release of livelihood assistance.

We reiterated that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
a. Inventory Committee to conduct a complete and proper physical inventory of the Municipality’s property and correspondingly prepare and submit to the Audit Team the required inventory report thereon. Any discrepancies noted between the inventory report and accounting and property records should be investigated and make the necessary adjustments to reconcile the PPE accounts;
b. concurrent General Services Officer to maintain a complete and updated property cards. The balance per property cards should always reconcile with the ledger cards of the accounting office to come out with an accurate and reliable balance of PPE accounts in the Municipality’s books;
c. Municipal Accountant to provide a complete Lapsing Schedule to support the PPE balances as well as the provision for Depreciation Expenses in the financial statements; and
d. GSO to prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) as basis for the proper disposal.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
a. Municipal Budget Officer to allocate at least five percent of the total budget appropriations for the implementation of GAD Plan;
b. GAD Focal Person of the Municipality to secure the review and endorsement of the DILG Provincial Office on the GPB disclosing the Agency’s programs, projects and activities designed to address the gender concerns of its constituents and to ensure the efficient utilization of the resources for the attainment of GAD objectives;
c. GAD Focal Person to ensure that the targets and accomplishments for GAD activities are quantified to facilitate monitoring and evaluation; and
d. GAD Focal Person to establish the details of the discrepancies between the GAD budgets and GAD Accomplishment Report and correct the entries accordingly.

We recommended management the following:
a] Issue official receipt to the concerned barangays the amount of ₱190,300.00 to support their disbursements;
b] Demand for the immediate recovery of the ₱190,300.00 from the collecting officer;
