We recommended that:
a] the GSO be required that stock cards be maintained and kept up-to-date for each item particularly drugs and medicines as well as Medical, Dental and Laboratory Supplies;
b] the Municipal Accounting Office record all purchases to its corresponding inventory account classification and to adjust this account for whatever consumption on the basis of Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI), duly supported with the original copy of Requisition Issue Slip (RIS).

We recommended that management:
